description: Returns the pull through cache rules for a registry.

parameters.name: ecrRepositoryPrefixes
parameters.description: The Amazon ECR repository prefixes associated with the pull through cache rules to return. If no repository prefix value is specified, all pull through cache rules are returned. (string) ---

nested_items.name: pullThroughCacheRules
nested_items.description: The details of the pull through cache rules.

nested_items.name: ecrRepositoryPrefix
nested_items.description: The Amazon ECR repository prefix associated with the pull through cache rule.

nested_items.name: upstreamRegistryUrl
nested_items.description: The upstream registry URL associated with the pull through cache rule.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The date and time the pull through cache was created.

nested_items.name: registryId
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services account ID associated with the registry the pull through cache rule is associated with.

nested_items.name: credentialArn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the Secrets Manager secret associated with the pull through cache rule.

nested_items.name: customRoleArn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the IAM role associated with the pull through cache rule.

nested_items.name: upstreamRepositoryPrefix
nested_items.description: The upstream repository prefix associated with the pull through cache rule.

nested_items.name: upstreamRegistry
nested_items.description: The name of the upstream source registry associated with the pull through cache rule.

nested_items.name: updatedAt
nested_items.description: The date and time, in JavaScript date format, when the pull through cache rule was last updated.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: The nextToken value to include in a future DescribePullThroughCacheRulesRequest request. When the results of a DescribePullThroughCacheRulesRequest request exceed maxResults, this value can be used to retrieve the next page of results. This value is null when there are no more results to return.
